                    <h1>2020 Extended School Closure Updates </h1>
                    <h2></h2>
                    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bricolage will continue to keep our community updated as the state of the COVID-19 virus and its impact on our programming and services evolve. </span></p>
<p><strong>Communications from Bricolage: </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>We are resuming our weekly Bricolage Family Announcements schedule. You will receive our Weekly Announcements every Wednesday evening.
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="https://mailchi.mp/3db5c1b2d461/bricolage-family-announcements_march-11-1327461?e=2d392cf69e" data-anchor="?e=2d392cf69e">Bricolage Family Announcements, April 1, 2020</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="https://mailchi.mp/3db5c1b2d461/bricolage-family-announcements_march-11-1327461?e=2d392cf69e" data-anchor="?e=2d392cf69e"></a><a href="https://mailchi.mp/ce3041acff41/bricolage-family-announcements_march-11-1327465?e=2d392cf69e" data-anchor="?e=2d392cf69e">Bricolage COVID-19 Update: April 3, 2020</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Should we receive important/immediate information, we will update families through email and social media platforms.</li>
<li>You will receive weekly contact from your child's teacher. Should you no longer want to receive frequent communication from your child’s teacher during this time, please <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1-KWhYpGGC1nac6H2eiWW_Ii54CqhZHnGoxsDp7CwLWE">click here to opt out.</a> </li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our website will house all updates and resources here. This page will be reviewed and updated as needed by school administration. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;">
<span style="font-weight: 400;">You can keep up with Bricolage updates through our Instagram (@BricolageNOLA) and Facebook page (</span><a href="http://www.facebook.com/BricolageNOLA"><span style="font-weight: 400;">www.facebook.com/BricolageNOLA</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">).</span>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you should have any questions regarding the content below, please contact </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">info@bricolagenola.org</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or front office cell phone at 504-250-5719.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Instructional Materials During Extended School Closure:</strong></p>
<p><span>All Pre-K-6th grade extended school closure instructional materials from March 16th - April 10th can be found </span><a rel="noopener" href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1-MFUVVDR1iDak1s70sWjpXbhm1RwhYc8" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1-MFUVVDR1iDak1s70sWjpXbhm1RwhYc8">here</a><span>.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>Click your child’s grade level folder to access instructional materials. Materials include student work packets for March 16th - April 30th, and additional resources like sample at home schedules. </span><br><span> </span><br><span>Families can access materials electronically or request a copy of the materials via mail by sending your child’s name, grade, and preferred mailing address to info@bricolagenola.org or calling 504-250-5719.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>Please note that 2</span><sup>nd</sup><span> through 6</span><sup>th</sup><span> grade student work packets DO NOT have to be completed on hard copies of the workbooks. Student work can be completed on any paper you have at home. </span><br><span> </span><br><span>Pre-k through 1st grade packets DO include activities that require a printed copy of the packet to complete.</span></p>
<p><strong>Please note that given the continued spread of the COVID-19 virus, Bricolage will no longer expect students to return their completed packets once in-person school sessions resume. </strong></p>
<p><a rel="noopener" href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1-MFUVVDR1iDak1s70sWjpXbhm1RwhYc8" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1-MFUVVDR1iDak1s70sWjpXbhm1RwhYc8">Find Grade Level Instructional Materials Here. </a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>YouTube Channels:</strong></p>
<p><span>In addition to student work packets, each grade level has created a grade level specific YouTube channel.</span><br><br><span>These channels will provide students with fun videos to supplement the work they are doing at home. Students ARE NOT required to watch videos. These channels are strictly supplemental tools that you can use to further engage your student(s).</span><br><br><span>New videos will be uploaded to these channels weekly. You are able to access these videos on your phone, tablet or computer.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>Please find the links to your child’s grade level YouTube channel below. </span></p>
<ul>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCtA3NGalb0xQAGLUCbH6B9Q/" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCtA3NGalb0xQAGLUCbH6B9Q/">Pre-K YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UClsyNhlO5m6JuMz1uL1KYMA?view_as=subscriber" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UClsyNhlO5m6JuMz1uL1KYMA?view_as=subscriber">K YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCn3SkdvgEKjGzsTZ90XauYQ/" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCn3SkdvgEKjGzsTZ90XauYQ/">1st YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnQg-Fj7f1v2AcHXl_FNY8g/" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnQg-Fj7f1v2AcHXl_FNY8g/">2nd YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC3vdCVOQu91oioqJF63RyQQ/videos?view_as=subscriber" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC3vdCVOQu91oioqJF63RyQQ/videos?view_as=subscriber">3rd YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCji14jmpYJYaCg5qnrSyt9Q?view_as=subscriber" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCji14jmpYJYaCg5qnrSyt9Q?view_as=subscriber">4th YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdo9w9P3iFdoXjEu3wXha_Q?view_as=subscriber" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdo9w9P3iFdoXjEu3wXha_Q?view_as=subscriber">5th YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCa9nwkbf8HOd2EWX3elm0gw/videos?view_as=subscriber" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdo9w9P3iFdoXjEu3wXha_Q?view_as=subscriber" data-anchor="?view_as=subscriber">6th YouTube Channel</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCaVTFSTE3Lv0NFN7hxS-sTw/featured" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCaVTFSTE3Lv0NFN7hxS-sTw/featured">Workshop with Ms. Whitney</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCJQxKIyg5Ko8cGt1PTSWwwQ" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCJQxKIyg5Ko8cGt1PTSWwwQ">Spanish with La Maestra YouTube Channel</a></li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Co-curricular Virtual Hangouts:</strong></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The co-curricular team is excited to host virtual hangouts for all students in grades 3-6. Below, you will find each teacher’s name with a corresponding date/time. Each call will be thirty minutes and will be designed to check in and facilitate conversation with students. These are OPTIONAL to families and intended for kids to reconnect with teachers and classmates.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To access, click on the link offered to each teacher and that should direct you to the room. The links will not be active until 10 minutes before the scheduled time and</span> you will now need to enter the matching password to enter<span style="font-weight: 400;">. If early, your child will wait until the teacher invites everyone in at scheduled time. Email co-curricular teacher directly if you have any questions or concerns.</span></p>
<p><a rel="noopener" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1r7IpLQN0YKzaWisyxmyjzdNJMs105czOPeLN0dEI4Fo/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank" data-anchor="?usp=sharing"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Find the schedule here.</span></a></p>
<p><strong>Technology Access:</strong></p>
<p><span>NOLA-PS has allocated </span><span class="il">Bricolage</span><span> Academy 75 Chromebooks and 61 hotspots.</span><br><br><span>Given the limited quantity, we are prioritizing students whose education plan requires them to utilize technology to fully access their education services. Devices will be distributed to identified </span><span class="il">families</span><span> this week. </span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Resources:</strong></p>
<p><span>There are numerous resources citywide to assist individuals and families during this time. To access a list of resources, </span><a href="https://nolapublicschools.com/community" data-cke-saved-href="https://nolapublicschools.com/community">please click here</a><span>.</span><br><br><span>Please note that many schools throughout the city are observing Spring Break over the next several days which may have an impact on community feeding site locations. Should you need assistance traveling to community feeding location, lyft has provided a code (CV19NOLAPS20) to provide families with free rides to community feeding sites.</span><br><br><span>Should you need any assistance, please contact our Bricolage Social Worker, Mr. Cantrel Larkins at </span><a>clarkins@bricolagenola.org</a><span> or our Bricolage School Counselor, Mrs. Mariel Aken at </span><a>maken@bricolagenola.org</a><span>.  </span></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://ready.nola.gov/incident/coronavirus/resources/?fbclid=IwAR3L_3kZn6KMXj-AIsvy6F048V4of2HEd4GdypUuy1QRMHLrc3cLjqLkl0I"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The City of New Orleans, NOLA Ready - Assistance for Residence </span></a></li>
<li><a href="https://nolapublicschools.com/covid19/nutrition"><span style="font-weight: 400;">NOLA PS Child Nutrition Programs</span></a></li>
<li><a href="https://nolapublicschools.com/coronavirus-updates"><span style="font-weight: 400;">NOLA Public Schools Coronavirus Updates Page</span></a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.louisianabelieves.com/resources/covid-19"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Louisiana Department of Education COVID-19 Update and Resources</span></a></li>
<li><a href="https://mailchi.mp/nsno/coronavirusupdatesmarch25-2872522?e=273366f1ab" data-anchor="?e=273366f1ab"><span style="font-weight: 400;">NSNO Resource Email</span></a></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">NORD, in partnership with Share Our Strength/No Kid Hungry Louisiana, is offering hot meals from 4pm-6pm at all of our rec centers except Annunciation Rec Center.  <a rel="noopener" href="https://nordc.org/getattachment/Homepage-Alerts/Second-Harvest/NORD-Feeding-Sites_2020.pdf/?lang=en-US" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://nordc.org/getattachment/Homepage-Alerts/Second-Harvest/NORD-Feeding-Sites_2020.pdf/?lang%3Den-US&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584735576199000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEBuQQwvKYNcG5iSIN3Cn9wTf0bCg" data-cke-saved-href="https://nordc.org/getattachment/Homepage-Alerts/Second-Harvest/NORD-Feeding-Sites_2020.pdf/?lang=en-US">Click here to find</a> locations near you.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">There are several resources available to persons who need assistance obtaining internet services. Charter Communications will offer free Spectrum broadband and Wi-Fi access for 60 days to households with K-12 and/or college students who do not already have a subscription. <a rel="noopener" href="https://internetessentials.com/" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://internetessentials.com/" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://internetessentials.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584562635262000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGmMhBD56ndVe4PUL-lUUbzx10mXQ">Click here</a> for more details.<br><br>Additionally, limited income households can apply for $5 to $10 per month internet access provided by <a rel="noopener" href="https://m.att.com/shopmobile/internet/access/" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://m.att.com/shopmobile/internet/access/" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://m.att.com/shopmobile/internet/access/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584562635262000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEFYVRN_rdQPO2bF9TGQVDyr2aJ_Q">AT&amp;T Access</a>, <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.cox.com/residential/internet/connect2compete.html" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.cox.com/residential/internet/connect2compete.html" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.cox.com/residential/internet/connect2compete.html&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584562635262000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGJpLVP2Uyv7L0GxRDm24A53dZCBg">Cox Connect2Compete</a>, and <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.centurylink.com/aboutus/community/community-development/lifeline.html" target="_blank" data-cke-saved-href="https://www.centurylink.com/aboutus/community/community-development/lifeline.html" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.centurylink.com/aboutus/community/community-development/lifeline.html&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584562635262000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHVvI42jtD5gCS3Ca9bbPE16KGWLA">CenturyLink Lifeline</a>. </span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you know of resources that will be useful for our community, please email information to info@bricolagenola.org.</span></p>
